adjectives.description: chichi (comparative more chichi, superlative most chichi)

entries.meaning: (mildly derogatory) Affectedly trendy; chic and stylish in a pretentious way.
(slang, Latin America, chiefly in the plural) A woman's breast.
examples: And later, in Latin Grill Express, Jesus makes sure to compliment her accent, her vocabulary, to express admiration for the way her chichis looked in the last dress all over again, then Sarah asks about his plans for work, what he will do when they all leave.
